fields.title: Say It Aint So
fields.content:
[Intro]

[ch]Am[/ch]  [ch]E[/ch]  [ch]F[/ch]  [ch]C[/ch]  x2

[ch]Am[/ch]       [ch]E[/ch]  [ch]F[/ch]  [ch]C[/ch]
Oh yeah.
[ch]Am[/ch]       [ch]E[/ch]  [ch]F[/ch]  [ch]C[/ch]
All right.


[Verse 1]

[ch]Am[/ch]         [ch]E[/ch]         [ch]F[/ch]           [ch]C[/ch]
Somebody's Heine' is crowdin' my icebox
[ch]Am[/ch]         [ch]E[/ch]           [ch]F[/ch]         [ch]C[/ch]
Somebody's cold one is givin' me chills
[ch]Am[/ch]              [ch]E[/ch]        [ch]F[/ch]    [ch]C[/ch]
Guess I'll just close my eyes


[Interlude]

   [ch]Am[/ch]   [ch]E[/ch]    [ch]F[/ch]     [ch]C[/ch]
Oh yeah,   alright
      [ch]Am[/ch]   [ch]E[/ch]    [ch]F[/ch]   [ch]C[/ch]
Feels good,  inside


[Verse 2]

[ch]Am[/ch]          [ch]E[/ch]      [ch]F[/ch]            [ch]C[/ch]
Flip on the tele', wrestle with Jimmy
[ch]Am[/ch]           [ch]E[/ch]        [ch]F[/ch]         [ch]C[/ch]
Something is bubbling behind my back
    [ch]Am[/ch]        [ch]E[/ch]        [ch]F[/ch]     [ch]C[/ch]
The bottle is ready to blow


[Chorus]

[ch]Am[/ch] [ch]E[/ch]  [ch]F[/ch]            [ch]C[/ch]
      Say it ain't so
[ch]Am[/ch]      [ch]E[/ch]         [ch]F[/ch]        [ch]C[/ch]
   Your drug is a heartbreaker
[ch]Am[/ch] [ch]E[/ch]  [ch]F[/ch]            [ch]C[/ch]
      Say it ain't so
[ch]Am[/ch]      [ch]E[/ch]       [ch]F[/ch]      [ch]C[/ch]
   My love is a lifetaker


[Interlude]

[ch]Am[/ch]  [ch]E[/ch]  [ch]F[/ch]  [ch]C[/ch]  x2


[Verse 3]

[ch]Am[/ch]         [ch]E[/ch]          [ch]F[/ch]       [ch]C[/ch]
I can't confront you, I never could do
[ch]Am[/ch]               [ch]E[/ch]            [ch]F[/ch]          [ch]C[/ch]
That which might hurt you, so try and be cool
          [ch]Am[/ch]      [ch]E[/ch]        [ch]F[/ch]                            [ch]C[/ch]
When I say - This way is a waterslide away from me that takes you further every
[ch]Am[/ch]   [ch]E[/ch]           [ch]F[/ch]     [ch]C[/ch]
day (hey), so be cool


[Chorus]

[ch]Am[/ch] [ch]E[/ch]  [ch]F[/ch]            [ch]C[/ch]
      Say it ain't so
[ch]Am[/ch]      [ch]E[/ch]         [ch]F[/ch]        [ch]C[/ch]
   Your drug is a heartbreaker
[ch]Am[/ch] [ch]E[/ch]  [ch]F[/ch]            [ch]C[/ch]
      Say it ain't so
[ch]Am[/ch]      [ch]E[/ch]       [ch]F[/ch]      [ch]C[/ch]
   My love is a lifetaker


[Bridge]

[ch]G[/ch]            [ch]G/F#[/ch]           [ch]C[/ch]            [ch]Eb[/ch]
   Dear Daddy,   I write you in spite of years of silence.
[ch]G[/ch]                    [ch]G/F#[/ch]           [ch]C[/ch]                [ch]Eb[/ch]
   You've cleaned up,   found Jesus, things are good or so I hear.
[ch]G[/ch]             [ch]G/F#[/ch]           [ch]C[/ch]         [ch]Eb[/ch]
   This bottle   of Steven's   awakens ancient feelings.
[ch]G[/ch]              [ch]G/F#[/ch]          [ch]C[/ch]             [ch]Eb[/ch]              [ch]Am[/ch]   [ch]E[/ch]
   Like father,   stepfather,   the son is drowning in the floooooood
[ch]F[/ch]                  [ch]C[/ch]
   Yeah, yeah yeah, yeah yeah.


[Solo]

[ch]Am[/ch]  [ch]E[/ch]  [ch]F[/ch]  [ch]C[/ch]  x3


[Chorus]

[ch]Am[/ch] [ch]E[/ch]  [ch]F[/ch]            [ch]C[/ch]
      Say it ain't so
[ch]Am[/ch]      [ch]E[/ch]         [ch]F[/ch]        [ch]C[/ch]
   Your drug is a heartbreaker
[ch]Am[/ch] [ch]E[/ch]  [ch]F[/ch]            [ch]C[/ch]
      Say it ain't so
[ch]Am[/ch]      [ch]E[/ch]       [ch]F[/ch]      [ch]C[/ch]
   My love is a lifetaker


[Outro]

[ch]Am[/ch]  [ch]E[/ch]  [ch]F[/ch]  [ch]C[/ch]  x2

fields.title: El Scorcho
fields.content:
This is a good song for only 1 guitar. But, if you want a 2nd guitar, have them strum 
open chords during the choruses and bridge and you pick the verses and choruses and strum 
barred chords during the bridge


During the Verse and Chorus, these chords are picked
      [ch]A[/ch]                 [ch]D[/ch]              [ch]E[/ch]
e|----------|      |----------|   |----------|
B|----------|      |-----7v---|   |----------|
G|-----6v---|      |-------7--|   |----------|
D|-------7--|      |---7------|   |----------|
A|---7------|      |-5--------|   |-7-5------|
E|-5--------|      |----------|   |-----9-7--|


During Bridge, these chords are strummed
   [ch]A[/ch]           [ch]D[/ch]          [ch]Bm[/ch]          [ch]E[/ch]
E: 5        E: 5       E: 7        E: 7
B: 5        B: 7       B: 7        B: 9
G: 6        G: 7       G: 7        G: 9
D: 7        D: 7       D: 9        D: 9
A: 7        A: 5       A: 9        A: 7
E: 5        E: X       E: 7        E: X


[Intro]

[ch]A[/ch] [ch]D[/ch] [ch]A[/ch] [ch]D[/ch] [ch]A[/ch] [ch]D[/ch] [ch]A[/ch]


[Verse 1]

      [ch]D[/ch]            [ch]A[/ch]              [ch]D[/ch]
Well, Goddamn you half-Japanese girls
[ch]A[/ch]                   [ch]D[/ch]
Do it to me every time
     [ch]A[/ch]                    [ch]D[/ch]
Oh, the redhead said you shred the cello
     [ch]A[/ch]          [ch]D[/ch]
And I'm jello, baby
     [ch]A[/ch]               [ch]D[/ch]
But you won't talk, won't look, won't think of me
[ch]A[/ch]                [ch]D[/ch]
I'm the epitome of Public Enemy


Why you wanna go and do me like that?
Come down on the street and dance with me


[Chorus]

[ch]A[/ch]   [ch]D[/ch]      [ch]A[/ch]        [ch]D[/ch]        [ch]A[/ch]      [ch]D[/ch]         [ch]A[/ch]         [ch]E[/ch]
I'm a lot like you so please Hello, I'm here, I'm waiting
[ch]A[/ch]  [ch]D[/ch]           [ch]A[/ch]    [ch]D[/ch]        [ch]A[/ch]        [ch]D[/ch]           [ch]A[/ch]     [ch]E[/ch]
I think I'd be good for you and you'd be good for me


[Verse 2]

               [ch]A[/ch]                   [ch]D[/ch]
I asked you to go to the Green Day concert
    [ch]A[/ch]                       [ch]D[/ch]
You said you never heard of them
    [ch]A[/ch]
How cool is that??
   [ch]D[/ch]                       [ch]A[/ch]             [ch]D[/ch]
So I went to your room and read your diary:
 [ch]A[/ch]                        [ch]D[/ch]                    [ch]A[/ch]
""watching Grunge leg-drop New-Jack trough presstable...""
    [ch]D[/ch]
and then my heart stopped:

""listening to Cio-Cio San
fall in love all over again.""


[Chorus]

[ch]A[/ch]   [ch]D[/ch]      [ch]A[/ch]        [ch]D[/ch]        [ch]A[/ch]      [ch]D[/ch]         [ch]A[/ch]         [ch]E[/ch]
I'm a lot like you so please Hello, I'm here, I'm waiting
[ch]A[/ch]  [ch]D[/ch]           [ch]A[/ch]    [ch]D[/ch]        [ch]A[/ch]        [ch]D[/ch]           [ch]A[/ch]     [ch]E[/ch]
I think I'd be good for you and you'd be good for me


[Bridge]

(Chords are strummed at double time[count 1,&,2,&,3,&,4,& for each strum], not finger 
like in the verses and chorus)

    [ch]A[/ch]                     [ch]D[/ch]
How stupid is it? I can't talk about it
        [ch]Bm[/ch]                       [ch]E[/ch]
I gotta sing about it and make a record of (my heart)
    [ch]A[/ch]                       [ch]D[/ch]
How stupid is it? won't you gimme a minute
       [ch]Bm[/ch]               [ch]E[/ch]
just come up to me and say ""hello"" to (my heart)

(Chords are now strummed at regular time [count 1,2,3,4 for each strum])

     [ch]A[/ch]             [ch]D[/ch]              [ch]Bm[/ch]
How stupid is it? For all I know you want me too
    [ch]E[/ch]                          [ch]A[/ch]
And maybe you just don't know what to do
    [ch]D[/ch]            [ch]Bm[/ch]             [ch]E[/ch]
Or maybe you're scared to say: ""I'm falling for you""


[Solo]
